1 (c) A nonpublic school enrolling more than 25 students in any grade whose tuition and
2 fees are paid in whole or in part with a scholarship grant shall provide and retain information on
3 student test performance in each grade with more than 25 students, as follows:
4 (1) Report to the Authority on the aggregate standardized test performance of
5 eligible students in grades three, eight, three through eight and 11. Aggregate
6 test performance data reported to the Authority which does not contain
7 personally identifiable student data shall be a public record under Chapter 132
8 of the General Statutes. Test performance data may be shared with public or
9 private institutions of higher education located in North Carolina and shall be
10 provided to an independent research organization selected by the Authority
11 for research purposes as permitted by the Federal Education Rights and
12 Privacy Act, 20 U.S.C. § 1232g.
13 (2) Retain standardized test performance data for eligible students in all other
14 grades and annually certify to the Authority compliance with the requirements
15 of subdivision (4) of subsection (a) of this section.
16 …."
17 SECTION 1.(b) The Office of Learning Research at The University of North
18 Carolina shall study and report the following to the Joint Legislative Education Oversight
19 Committee by December 31, 2026:
20 (1) For the purpose of comparing student performance, recommendations for
21 nationally standardized tests for use in third grade through eighth grade that
22 would be appropriate for administering to (i) students in nonpublic schools
23 who are receiving Opportunity Scholarships beginning with the 2027-2028
24 school year and (ii) students attending schools in public school units. The
25 Office of Learning Research shall recommend only one test for use in each
26 grade.
27 (2) Alignment between the nationally standardized tests selected pursuant to
28 subdivision (1) of this subsection and the standard course of study for third
29 grade through eighth grade, respectively, including a crosswalk between the
30 standards assessed by the nationally standardized tests and the standard course
31 of study.
32 (3) Feasibility of developing a through-grade assessment for third through eighth
33 grade that would meet the following criteria:
34 a. Assess mastery of the standard course of study.
35 b. Consist of multiple testing events throughout the year that are
36 aggregated into a summative score.
37 c. Replace the current end-of-grade assessments for third and eighth
38 grade.
39 d. Yield data that can be used with the Education Value-Added
40 Assessment System (EVAAS).
41 e. Comply with federal law.
42 SECTION 1.(c) The State Education Assistance Authority shall designate as the
43 nationally standardized assessments to be administered by nonpublic schools, in accordance with
44 G.S. 115C-562.5(a)(4), the tests recommended by the Office of Learning Research at The
45 University of North Carolina for use in third grade through eighth grade in accordance with
46 subsection (b) of this section.
47 SECTION 1.(d) Notwithstanding G.S. 115C-562.5(a)(1), for the report required
48 pursuant to G.S. 115C-562.5(a)(1) for the 2026-2027 school year, the nonpublic school shall also
49 provide documentation for required tuition and fees charged to students receiving scholarship
50 grant funds under Part 2A of Article 39 of Chapter 115C of the General Statutes by the nonpublic
51 school for the 2024-2025 and 2025-2026 school years.
